#. <section class="sutta" id="sn46.56"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn46.56:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 46"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 46"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn46.56:0.2"
msgid "6. Sākacchavagga"
msgstr "6. Discussion"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn46.56:0.3"
msgid "56. Abhayasutta"
msgstr "56. A Place Without Fear"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.127"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.56:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn46.56:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak "
"Mountain."

msgctxt "sn46.56:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho abhayo rājakumāro yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho abhayo "
"rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Prince Abhaya went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and "
"said to him:"

msgctxt "sn46.56:1.4"
msgid "“pūraṇo, bhante, kassapo evamāha:"
msgstr "“Sir, Pūraṇa Kassapa says this:"

msgctxt "sn46.56:1.5"
msgid "‘natthi hetu, natthi paccayo aññāṇāya adassanāya."
msgstr "‘There is no cause or condition for not knowing and not seeing."

#. VAR: appaccayo → appaccayā (bj) | apaccayo (s1, pts1) | appaccayaṃ (?)
msgctxt "sn46.56:1.6"
msgid "Ahetu, appaccayo aññāṇaṃ adassanaṃ hoti."
msgstr "Not knowing and not seeing have no cause or condition."

msgctxt "sn46.56:1.7"
msgid "Natthi hetu, natthi paccayo ñāṇāya dassanāya."
msgstr "There is no cause or condition for knowing and seeing."

msgctxt "sn46.56:1.8"
msgid "Ahetu, appaccayo ñāṇaṃ dassanaṃ hotī’ti."
msgstr "Knowing and seeing have no cause or condition.’"

msgctxt "sn46.56:1.9"
msgid "Idha bhagavā kimāhā”ti?"
msgstr "What does the Buddha say about this?”"

msgctxt "sn46.56:1.10"
msgid "“Atthi, rājakumāra, hetu, atthi paccayo aññāṇāya adassanāya."
msgstr ""
"“Prince, there are causes and conditions for not knowing and not seeing."

#. VAR: sappaccayo → sappaccayā (bj) | sapaccayo (pts1) | sappaccayaṃ (?)
msgctxt "sn46.56:1.11"
msgid "Sahetu, sappaccayo aññāṇaṃ adassanaṃ hoti."
msgstr "Not knowing and not seeing have causes and conditions."

msgctxt "sn46.56:1.12"
msgid "Atthi, rājakumāra, hetu, atthi paccayo ñāṇāya dassanāya."
msgstr "There are causes and conditions for knowing and seeing."

msgctxt "sn46.56:1.13"
msgid "Sahetu, sappaccayo ñāṇaṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti."
msgstr "Knowing and seeing have causes and conditions.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.56:2.1"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, hetu, katamo paccayo aññāṇāya adassanāya?"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, what is the cause and condition for not knowing and not seeing?"

msgctxt "sn46.56:2.2"
msgid "Kathaṃ sahetu, sappaccayo aññāṇaṃ adassanaṃ hotī”ti?"
msgstr "How do not knowing and not seeing have causes and conditions?”"

msgctxt "sn46.56:2.3"
msgid ""
"“Yasmiṃ kho, rājakumāra, samaye kāmarāgapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati "
"kāmarāgaparetena, uppannassa ca kāmarāgassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ na jānāti "
"na passati—"
msgstr ""
"“There’s a time when the heart is overcome and mired in sensual desire, "
"without truly knowing and seeing the escape from sensual desire that has "
"arisen."

msgctxt "sn46.56:2.4"
msgid "ayampi kho, rājakumāra, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo aññāṇāya adassanāya."
msgstr "This is a cause and condition for not knowing and not seeing."

msgctxt "sn46.56:2.5"
msgid "Evampi sahetu sappaccayo aññāṇaṃ adassanaṃ hoti."
msgstr "And this is how not knowing and not seeing have causes and conditions."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.56:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, rājakumāra, yasmiṃ samaye byāpādapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā "
"viharati byāpādaparetena … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, there’s a time when the heart is overcome and mired in ill will "
"…"

msgctxt "sn46.56:3.2"
msgid "thinamiddhapariyuṭṭhitena … pe …"
msgstr "dullness and drowsiness …"

msgctxt "sn46.56:3.3"
msgid "uddhaccakukkuccapariyuṭṭhitena … pe …"
msgstr "restlessness and remorse …"

msgctxt "sn46.56:3.4"
msgid ""
"vicikicchāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati vicikicchāparetena, uppannāya ca "
"vicikicchāya nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ na jānāti na passati—"
msgstr ""
"doubt, without truly knowing and seeing the escape from doubt that has "
"arisen."

msgctxt "sn46.56:3.5"
msgid "ayampi kho, rājakumāra, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo aññāṇāya adassanāya."
msgstr "This is a cause and condition for not knowing and not seeing."

msgctxt "sn46.56:3.6"
msgid "Evampi sahetu sappaccayo aññāṇaṃ adassanaṃ hotī”ti."
msgstr "And this is how not knowing and not seeing have causes and conditions.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.56:4.1"
msgid "“Ko nāmāyaṃ, bhante, dhammapariyāyo”ti?"
msgstr "“Sir, what is the name of this exposition of the teaching?”"

msgctxt "sn46.56:4.2"
msgid "“Nīvaraṇā nāmete, rājakumārā”ti."
msgstr "“These are called the ‘hindrances’, prince.”"

msgctxt "sn46.56:4.3"
msgid "“Taggha, bhagavā, nīvaraṇā;"
msgstr "“Indeed, Blessed One, these are hindrances!"

msgctxt "sn46.56:4.4"
msgid "taggha, sugata, nīvaraṇā."
msgstr "Indeed, Holy One, these are hindrances!"

msgctxt "sn46.56:4.5"
msgid ""
"Ekamekenapi kho, bhante, nīvaraṇena abhibhūto yathābhūtaṃ na jāneyya na "
"passeyya, ko pana vādo pañcahi nīvaraṇehi?"
msgstr ""
"Overcome by even a single hindrance you wouldn’t truly know or see, how much "
"more so all five hindrances."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.128"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.56:5.1"
msgid "Katamo pana, bhante, hetu, katamo paccayo ñāṇāya dassanāya?"
msgstr "But sir, what is the cause and condition for knowing and seeing?"

msgctxt "sn46.56:5.2"
msgid "Kathaṃ sahetu, sappaccayo ñāṇaṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti?"
msgstr "How do knowing and seeing have causes and conditions?”"

msgctxt "sn46.56:5.3"
msgid ""
"“Idha, rājakumāra, bhikkhu satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ "
"virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"“It’s when a mendicant develops the awakening factor of mindfulness, which "
"relies on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripens as letting go."

msgctxt "sn46.56:5.4"
msgid "So satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāvitena cittena yathābhūtaṃ jānāti passati—"
msgstr ""
"They truly know and see with a mind that has developed the awakening factor "
"of mindfulness."

msgctxt "sn46.56:5.5"
msgid "ayampi kho, rājakumāra, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo ñāṇāya dassanāya."
msgstr "This is a cause and condition for knowing and seeing."

msgctxt "sn46.56:5.6"
msgid "Evampi sahetu, sappaccayo ñāṇaṃ dassanaṃ hoti."
msgstr "And this is how knowing and seeing have causes and conditions."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.56:6.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, rājakumāra, bhikkhu … pe … upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti "
"vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant develops the awakening factor of investigation of "
"principles ... energy ... rapture ... tranquility ... immersion ... "
"equanimity, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen "
"as letting go."

msgctxt "sn46.56:6.2"
msgid "So upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāvitena cittena yathābhūtaṃ jānāti passati—"
msgstr ""
"They truly know and see with a mind that has developed the awakening factor "
"of equanimity."

msgctxt "sn46.56:6.3"
msgid "ayampi kho, rājakumāra, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo ñāṇāya dassanāya."
msgstr "This is a cause and condition for knowing and seeing."

msgctxt "sn46.56:6.4"
msgid "Evaṃ sahetu, sappaccayo ñāṇaṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti."
msgstr "And this is how knowing and seeing have causes and conditions.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.56:7.1"
msgid "“Ko nāmāyaṃ, bhante, dhammapariyāyo”ti?"
msgstr "“Sir, what is the name of this exposition of the teaching?”"

msgctxt "sn46.56:7.2"
msgid "“Bojjhaṅgā nāmete, rājakumārā”ti."
msgstr "“These are called the ‘awakening factors’, prince.”"

msgctxt "sn46.56:7.3"
msgid "“Taggha, bhagavā, bojjhaṅgā;"
msgstr "“Indeed, Blessed One, these are awakening factors!"

msgctxt "sn46.56:7.4"
msgid "taggha, sugata, bojjhaṅgā."
msgstr "Indeed, Holy One, these are awakening factors!"

msgctxt "sn46.56:7.5"
msgid ""
"Ekamekenapi kho, bhante, bojjhaṅgena samannāgato yathābhūtaṃ jāneyya "
"passeyya, ko pana vādo sattahi bojjhaṅgehi?"
msgstr ""
"Endowed with even a single awakening factor you would truly know and see, "
"how much more so all seven awakening factors."

msgctxt "sn46.56:7.6"
msgid ""
"Yopi me, bhante, gijjhakūṭaṃ pabbataṃ ārohantassa kāyakilamatho "
"cittakilamatho, sopi me paṭippassaddho, dhammo ca me abhisamito”ti."
msgstr ""
"When climbing Mount Vulture’s Peak I became fatigued in body and mind. But "
"this has now faded away. And I’ve comprehended the teaching.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn46.56:7.7"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn46.56:7.8"
msgid "Sākacchavaggo chaṭṭho."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.56:8.1"
msgid "Āhārā pariyāyamaggi,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn46.56:8.2"
msgid "mettaṃ saṅgāravena ca;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn46.56:8.3"
msgid "Abhayo pucchito pañhaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn46.56:8.4"
msgid "gijjhakūṭamhi pabbateti."
msgstr ""
